message.entry: Eye Diagram requires a Communications System Toolbox license.
Varying the number of input channels is not allowed.
Inputs with more than two dimensions are not supported.
The input must be a scalar, column vector or Simulink 1-D signal. Multichannel inputs are not supported.

Eye Diagram cannot accept a bus as its input signal. Insert a Bus to Vector conversion block in the signal path or extract signals using a Bus Selector block. To view the options associated with this message, in the Configuration Parameters dialog box, select Diagnostics > Connectivity; under Buses, see Bus signal treated as vector.
The input data type must be double precision, single precision, or fixed point.
The number of input channels cannot exceed {0}.
An input value of the Eye Diagram block is outside the specified Y limits. Such values are ignored.
